From: OpenAI Codex <codex@openai.com>
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: freescale: dpaa: add Stage 2 FMAN object surface

Add the Stage 2 backend-private FMAN object surface for the exact
primary outbound hardware class without claiming live FMAN residency:

- keep the scope pinned to the exact eth2 outbound class with IPv4
  SNAT, Ethernet rewrite, VLAN 10 push, and PPPoE push
- tighten the Stage 2 egress gate to the validated WAN representation
  in-tree: lower redirect eth0 plus exact eth0.10 plus PPPoE push
- derive the staged FMAN TX enqueue binding from the resolved egress
  path instead of from the ingress port's local TX identity
- build explicit backend-private ingress, header-manipulation,
  enqueue, and stats surface objects on top of the Stage 1 plan and
  resource lifetime model
- keep software flow offloading unchanged and keep hardware-requested
  flows on the FMAN backend path with explicit live-commit-unavailable
  degradation
- expose Stage 2 counters, lifecycle state, and enqueue observability
  through ft_offload, including a preserved last-staged enqueue
  snapshot for post-teardown validation

This stops at the honest Stage 2 boundary. The in-tree seam still does
not expose live FMAN header-manipulation and enqueue commit APIs, so
mode.active remains non-hardware and traffic stays on the normal Linux
path when hardware is requested.

The last-staged enqueue snapshot is debug-only observability. The
live/current Stage 2 surface still tears down immediately, and this
patch still does not add any live FMAN commit surface.

